(FINANCIAL HIGHLIGHTS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Net interest margin \(NIM\) was 3.42% for Q3 2025, down slightly from 3.48% in Q2 2025,) Tj
T*
(reflecting a higher cost of interest-bearing deposits as customers continued to shift balances) Tj
T*
(into higher-yielding time deposit products. The efficiency ratio improved to 58.3% from 59.7%) Tj
T*
(in the prior quarter, reflecting continued cost discipline and modest revenue growth. Total) Tj
T*
(loan balances grew 4.2% quarter over quarter to $19.8 billion, while total deposits grew 2.6%) Tj
T*
(to $23.1 billion. Non-interest income was $41.7 million for the quarter, an increase of 6.4%) Tj
T*
(from Q2 2025, driven by higher wealth management fees and treasury services revenue.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CAPITAL AND LIQUIDITY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The Common Equity Tier 1 \(CET1\) capital ratio stood at 11.2% at quarter-end, comfortably above) Tj
T*
(the regulatory minimum, though down from 11.6% in Q2 2025 due to continued balance sheet growth) Tj
T*
(outpacing retained earnings. The Tier 1 capital ratio was 12.4%, and the total capital ratio) Tj
T*
(was 14.1%. The bank's leverage ratio was 9.3%. Liquidity coverage ratio \(LCR\) was 118%, and the) Tj
T*
(loan-to-deposit ratio increased to 85.7% from 83.9% in the prior quarter, reflecting faster) Tj
T*
(loan growth relative to deposit growth. The board approved a quarterly common stock dividend of) Tj
T*
($0.42 per share, consistent with the prior quarter.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
