T*
() Tj
T*
(The non-performing loan \(NPL\) ratio increased to 0.87% of total loans at quarter-end, up from) Tj
T*
(0.71% in Q2 2025, driven primarily by two large commercial real estate relationships in the) Tj
T*
(office sector that were downgraded during the quarter. Net charge-offs were 0.24% of average) Tj
T*
(loans on an annualized basis, up from 0.18% in the prior quarter. The provision for credit) Tj
T*
(losses was $18.6 million for the quarter, compared to $12.3 million in Q2 2025, reflecting both) Tj
T*
(loan growth and the deterioration noted above. The allowance for credit losses as a percentage) Tj
T*
(of total loans was 1.15% at quarter-end.) Tj
